 IoT-Based Health Monitoring System using ESP8266 & Blynk
Overview
This project integrates ESP8266, MAX30100, DHT11, and MQ2 Gas Sensor to create a real-time health monitoring system. The collected data is sent to the Blynk app, allowing remote monitoring of vital parameters.

Features
✅ Heart Rate & SpO2 Monitoring (MAX30100)
✅ Temperature & Humidity Detection (DHT11)
✅ Air Quality Monitoring (MQ2 Gas Sensor)
✅ Blynk App Integration for Remote Monitoring

🛠 Components Required
ESP8266 NodeMCU
MAX30100 Pulse Oximeter Sensor
DHT11 Temperature & Humidity Sensor
MQ2 Gas Sensor
Jumper Wires
🔌 Circuit Connections
Component	ESP8266 Pin
MAX30100 INT	D3
DHT11 Sensor	D4
MQ2 Sensor	A0

🚀 How to Use
1️⃣ Connect all components as per the circuit diagram.
2️⃣ Upload the code to ESP8266 using Arduino IDE.
3️⃣ Open the Blynk app, set up the virtual pins, and monitor data remotely.

🔗 Applications
✅ Remote Health Monitoring
✅ IoT-based Smart Healthcare
✅ Real-time Air Quality Tracking
